# Go module workflow (this repo)

**Scope:** Only when this repository uses Go. If there is no `go.mod`, ignore this file.

## Forbidden

- MUST NOT run `go mod init` or delete `go.mod` / `go.sum`.
- MUST NOT recreate module layout or duplicate Makefile targets that already exist.
- MUST NOT change import paths to "fix" tests without a stated reason.

## Required

- MUST use existing `go.mod`, `go.sum`, and Makefile targets (`make build`, `make test`, `make lint` when present).
- MUST run `go mod tidy` after adding or removing dependencies, then `go mod verify` when checking integrity.

## Commands

- Correct: `go mod tidy`, `make test`, `go build ./...`, `golangci-lint run` (if configured).
- Wrong: `go mod init new_module`, `rm go.mod go.sum`.

## On failure

- MUST fix test logic or application code, not the module skeleton.
- MUST add missing dependencies via `go.mod` and `go mod tidy`, not workarounds.
